(491, 'Publications - National Cancer Institute', 'Information about NCI publications including PDQ cancer information for patients and health professionals, patient-education publications, fact sheets, dictionaries, NCI blogs and newsletters and majo', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/publications', '8f9c04798ab54bf962c68c1c4e590462'),
(492, 'About Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Information from the National Cancer Institute about cancer treatment, prevention, screening, genetics, causes, and how to cope with cancer.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer', 'b2d53ffbf15b7462acf683c9a926ce0c'),
(493, 'Understanding Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'This page is a gateway to basic information about how cancer develops, trends in cancer cases and deaths, and how cancer affects different populations.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/understanding', '5f78e2252166eae98078f755d384a140'),
(494, 'What Is Cancer? - National Cancer Institute', 'Explanations about what cancer is, how cancer cells differ from normal cells, and genetic changes that cause cancer to grow and spread.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/understanding/what-is-cancer', '7eac3636a909ab02961fe9f3e743ff62'),
(495, 'Cancer Statistics - National Cancer Institute', 'Basic information about cancer statistics in the United States and how they are used to understand the impact of cancer on society and to develop strategies that address the challenges that cancer pos', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/understanding/statistics', 'c41dd1478bf84df8bddada05bd4636c5'),
(496, 'Cancer Disparities - National Cancer Institute', 'Basic information about cancer disparities in the U.S., factors that contribute to the disproportionate burden of cancer in some groups, and examples of disparities in incidence and mortality among ce', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/understanding/disparities', 'c09c48b36053334071c95b2775ab39d1'),
(497, 'Cancer Causes and Prevention - National Cancer Institute', 'Covers known cancer risk factors, how certain cancers can be prevented, and ongoing research into causes and prevention.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/causes-prevention', 'fba618b424452b057b929ef26054b7a3'),
(498, 'Risk Factors for Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Information about behaviors, exposures, and other factors that may influence the risk of cancer.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/causes-prevention/risk', '5736a25a023edda6f2b56182d2cc7b84'),
(499, 'The Genetics of Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Information about genetic changes, how they may be inherited or acquired during a person\'s life, how they can increase cancer risk, and genetic testing for mutations.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/causes-prevention/genetics', '07eec83828d55509c705dfaf46c081d2'),
(500, 'Cancer Prevention Overview (PDQ®)–Patient Version - National Cancer Institute', 'Cancer prevention methods include avoiding things that cause cancer, having a healthy lifestyle, getting screened, and using some medicines or surgery. Learn more about ways to help prevent cancer in ', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/causes-prevention/patient-prevention-overview-pdq', '2ab1fbda37c78d4374ab66bd18712a26'),
(501, 'Cancer Causes and Prevention Research - National Cancer Institute', 'Find the latest research articles on cancer causes and risk factors for cancers and how some cancers may be prevented.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/causes-prevention/research', 'bd56e9913770c5529c5b16dbce02263f'),
(502, 'Cancer Screening - National Cancer Institute', 'Cancer screening is checking for cancer in people who don\'t have symptoms. Screening tests can help doctors find and treat several types of cancer early, but cancer screening can have harms as well as', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/screening', '6949e1317d77be6743c5159e5dd92009'),
(503, 'Cancer Screening Overview (PDQ®)–Patient Version - National Cancer Institute', 'Cancer screening means looking for cancer before symptoms appear, when cancer may be easier to treat. Screening tests can help reduce the risk of dying from some cancers, but all tests have potential ', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/screening/patient-screening-overview-pdq', 'ddbd1259375fa7d4c8a563ab700d2586'),
(504, 'Screening Tests for Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Information about tests such as mammography and colonoscopy that may be used to screen for cancer in people without symptoms of disease.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/screening/screening-tests', '8176b4323b342e4dade12ac48fac0d25'),
(505, 'Cancer Screening Research - National Cancer Institute', 'Find research articles on cancer screening, which may include news stories, clinical trials, blog posts, and descriptions of active studies.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/screening/research', '93bd14efae9b7fd558aa7f1af0036a8a'),
(506, 'Diagnosis and Staging - National Cancer Institute', 'Cancer can cause many different symptoms. The doctor will order tests to determine if symptoms are caused by cancer or some other problem. If cancer is diagnosed, the doctor will run tests to determin', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/diagnosis-staging', '621344b925cc6fccf543ccd4e86b6d1c'),
(507, 'Symptoms of Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Cancer can cause different symptoms, such as abnormal bumps, night sweats, or unexplained weight gain or loss. Only a doctor can tell if symptoms are caused by cancer or some other problem.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/diagnosis-staging/symptoms', 'b7e84f559bc34a338e118ab7f9db4a21'),
(508, 'How Cancer Is Diagnosed - National Cancer Institute', 'Learn about tests and procedures that diagnose cancer. Your doctor may ask about personal and family medical history or order lab tests, imaging scans, or a biopsy.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/diagnosis-staging/diagnosis', 'be90d68313be3b45bec8b607cd243177'),
(509, 'Cancer Staging - National Cancer Institute', 'Staging is the process of determining how much cancer is within the body (tumor size) and if it has spread. Learn about the TNM Staging system and other ways that stage is described.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/diagnosis-staging/staging', '76c2193ebf89b7e0e3db3eb667c18555'),
(510, 'Understanding Cancer Prognosis - National Cancer Institute', 'Prognosis describes how serious your cancer is and your chances of survival. Learn about survival statistics and how they are used to estimate prognosis.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/diagnosis-staging/prognosis', '9399f68bccdccb4be4b9e8129c5ac960'),
(511, 'Questions to Ask Your Doctor about Your Diagnosis - National Cancer Institute', 'Suggested questions for patients to ask their doctors when they learn they have cancer and want to know what to expect next.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/diagnosis-staging/questions', '5e0c2b265e25ac9a7d8533648a9ba778'),
(512, 'Cancer Diagnosis and Staging Research - National Cancer Institute', 'Find research articles on cancer diagnosis and staging, which may include news stories, clinical trials, blog posts, and descriptions of active studies.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/diagnosis-staging/research', '149539cee380ffecdd5c1ca1535f2361'),
(513, 'Treatment for Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Information on cancer treatment methods, specific anticancer drugs, and drug development and approval. Research updates, cancer treatment facilities, and other topics also covered.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment', '3d6180d4146e61e8fc4923d3cc94d85e'),
(514, 'Types of Cancer Treatment - National Cancer Institute', 'This page lists the different cancer treatments, including chemotherapy, radiation therapy, immunotherapy, and targeted therapy and takes you to more information about each type.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/types', '01a14b45a87b32d9e50bd779b302869d'),
(515, 'Side Effects of Cancer Treatment - National Cancer Institute', 'Side effects are problems that occur when cancer treatment affects healthy tissues or organs. Learn about side effects caused by cancer treatment. Know what signs and symptoms to call your doctor abou', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/side-effects', '49f3de006c39fd342089ab2c5b6acddc'),
(516, 'Clinical Trials Information for Patients and Caregivers - National Cancer Institute', 'Explains clinical trials, including what they are, why they are important, things to think about when deciding to take part, and questions to ask your doctor.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/clinical-trials', 'e35c18c30c0652a3183aac263abda61e'),
(517, 'Cancer Drugs - National Cancer Institute', 'List of cancer drug information summaries providing details about cancer drugs and cancer drug combinations.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/drugs', '06504d72a7719020735e5b7de7adb2f6'),
(518, 'Complementary and Alternative Medicine (CAM) - National Cancer Institute', 'Types of healing approaches and therapies used in complementary and alternative medicine (CAM) in cancer care, talking to your doctor about CAM, safety of CAM', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/cam', 'a7afe4b3a9f932d073b27e28e6069efa'),
(519, 'Questions to Ask about Cancer Treatment - National Cancer Institute', 'Suggested questions for cancer patients to ask their doctors about treatment choices and the possible side effects of cancer treatment.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/questions', 'f894ea30094a7e553066016a41240b41'),
(520, 'Cancer Treatment Research - National Cancer Institute', 'Find research articles on cancer treatment, including news stories, clinical trials, blog posts, and descriptions of active studies.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/research', '8c94cd71189062efef26539ad63e61ff'),
(521, 'Coping With Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Information for patients, families, and caregivers to help manage emotional and lifestyle effects of cancer, treatment, and life after treatment.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping', '856a636e6474ea35a9399151d061e012'),
(522, 'Feelings and Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Ways to cope with your emotions and manage the emotional effects of cancer, including anger, fear, stress, and depression.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping/feelings', '17c9add433e9699d1bdbb15855c03d76'),
(523, 'Coping - Adjusting to Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Information that helps you and your family face life’s changes from cancer. Includes talking with your doctors, talking to children, changes for the family, and information on cancer support groups.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping/adjusting-to-cancer', 'e62baa16b67ce991c10648d9fa633ff5'),
(524, 'Self-Image, Sexuality, and Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Cancer and its treatment can change how you look and feel about yourself. Learn to cope with body changes and issues related to sexuality and intimacy.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping/self-image', '3ee008bd0b2f2bd28346e508ce76f67f'),
(525, 'Coping – Day-to-Day Life - National Cancer Institute', 'Enjoy life and stay active during and after cancer treatment. Get tips for keeping up with your daily routine, going back to work, and finding spiritual well-being.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping/day-to-day', '2dfe2f25e306d4dfce7b58ef30cf0770'),
(526, 'Caregivers of Cancer Patients - National Cancer Institute', 'Being a caregiver of cancer patients can be stressful. Find out what to expect and how to deal with caring for a loved one with cancer.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping/caregiver-support', '6764fca9a942361afe73dac201a7e240'),
(527, 'Coping – Cancer Survivorship - National Cancer Institute', 'Becoming a cancer survivor happens at the time of diagnosis. When cancer treatment ends, the transition to a new normal can be hard. Learn about follow-up care, coping with physical and emotional issu', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping/survivorship', '75654aa07d8bc46fb9ef1bfe95d28ff0'),
(528, 'Questions to Ask Your Doctor about Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Sets of questions, organized by topic, that cancer patients may want to ask their doctors or other members of their health care team to learn more about their cancer and what to expect.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping/questions', 'bb55576d4df859c3d0f7f1cccb74c8ab'),
(529, 'Research on Coping with Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Find research articles on coping with cancer, which may include news stories, clinical trials, blog posts, and descriptions of active studies.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coping/research', '6e7c70fe896119d13c2c64c3413f24e0');
