(530, 'Advanced Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Information to help with talking about and coping with advanced cancer, making choices about care, and planning for the end of life.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/advanced-cancer', 'f7a4d3ca6ef998ea4e21c4231a70abe3'),
(531, 'Choices for Care with Advanced Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Know your choices for cancer care when coping with terminal cancer. Learn about palliative care, hospice care, and trying a clinical trial.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/advanced-cancer/care-choices', '46bcd0dc656e1930135281e91e108783'),
(532, 'Talking to Others about Your Advanced Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Describes what questions to ask and what issues to talk about with your doctors when given an advanced cancer diagnosis. Also gives tips for talking with your spouse, kids, teenagers, and adult childr', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/advanced-cancer/talking', '5473360b50ac69a3158f0933c4d3d494'),
(533, 'Coping with Your Feelings - National Cancer Institute', 'Having an advanced or terminal cancer diagnosis can cause a range of feelings to cope with. Know that you\'re not alone. Learn tips on how to cope with your feelings with an advanced cancer diagnosis.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/advanced-cancer/feelings', '6c7f00849758aa7ddb477f650df624ee'),
(534, 'Planning for Advanced Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Find out what issues need to be addressed when dealing with an advanced or metastatic cancer diagnosis. Completing advance directives, looking at health insurance, organizing records and documents, an', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/advanced-cancer/planning', '98e1d486e999d32555d6913c2097b8ef'),
(535, 'Advanced Cancer and Caregivers - National Cancer Institute', 'Learn tips for taking care of yourself, coping with your feelings and grief, asking for help, communicating with your loved one about their wishes for care, talking to children about death.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/advanced-cancer/caregivers', 'c130a18199b3a993641d6ad6f6b78c17'),
(536, 'Questions to Ask about Advanced Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Suggested questions to ask your doctor, if you find out you have advanced cancer.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/advanced-cancer/questions', '41fb4676922f11f77b146035a72da82f'),
(537, 'Advanced Cancer Research - National Cancer Institute', 'Find research articles on advanced cancer, which may include news stories, clinical trials, blog posts, and descriptions of active studies.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/advanced-cancer/research', '8e5dbd9c482a0ccb73136ce1677b30ec'),
(538, 'Managing Cancer Care - National Cancer Institute', 'Information on choosing a doctor or treatment facility, home care, financial help, insurance coverage, end-of-life planning, and resources to help you avoid scams.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/managing-care', 'be2248490893829a6578fe8b9e81cdd2'),
(539, 'Finding Health Care Services - National Cancer Institute', 'If you have been diagnosed with cancer, finding a doctor and treatment facility for your cancer care is an important step to getting the best treatment possible. Learn tips for choosing a doctor and t', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/managing-care/services', '8bc1d20328e75d8c98e523db11a676a7'),
(540, 'Managing Costs and Medical Information - National Cancer Institute', 'People with cancer may face major financial challenges and need help dealing with the high costs of care. Cancer treatment can be very expensive, even when you have insurance. Learn ways to manage med', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/managing-care/track-care-costs', 'fe08e3f52d971e0cb0edb802a70d9470'),
(541, 'Managing Cancer Care - Advance Directives - National Cancer Institute', 'Advance directives are legal documents that allow you to decide ahead of time what kind of medical care you want or who you want to make decisions for you if you\'re too ill to speak for yourself.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/managing-care/advance-directives', 'e1c478fdbbe99dd595da08b8ad24102d'),
(542, 'How to Find Cancer Resources You Can Trust - National Cancer Institute', 'Information to help people understand how to look for trusted cancer information online and how to evaluate the source and credibility of health information that they find online in websites and socia', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/managing-care/using-trusted-resources', '87188c612b6fa9fdc2e8392fe6c0d9bf'),
(543, 'Coronavirus and Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Information about coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19), including what patients with cancer should know about the virus, how the pandemic may affect cancer care, research studies for patients with canc', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coronavirus', '6d2f4477c8614c33e2497cc0ee60f732'),
(544, 'Coronavirus: What People with Cancer Should Know - National Cancer Institute', 'Some cancer treatments may increase your risk of severe illness from COVID-19. Learn about how patients with cancer can protect themselves and what they should do if they have symptoms of an infection', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coronavirus/coronavirus-cancer-patient-information', '385a46305a58084fbca591a8db3f3c38'),
(545, 'Cancer Clinical Trials during Coronavirus - National Cancer Institute', 'NCI coordinates and supports cancer clinical trials at more than 2,200 sites across the United States, Canada, and internationally. Learn how the COVID-19 pandemic has affected the operations of NCI-s', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/coronavirus/coronavirus-impact-clinical-trials', '79e29d77db350185eeb6ad02278ea85d'),
(546, 'Side Effects of Cancer Treatment - National Cancer Institute', 'Side effects are problems that occur when cancer treatment affects healthy tissues or organs. Learn about side effects caused by cancer treatment. Know what signs and symptoms to call your doctor abou', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/side-effects/', 'e5cf7b3a424ed2826f8e64565aa02c2f'),
(547, 'A to Z List of Cancer Types - National Cancer Institute', 'Alphabetical list of all cancers, with links to disease-specific and general information about treatment, coping, screening, prevention, clinical trials, and other topics.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/types', '1001c040afaca387fe4217a3a561d592'),
(548, 'Adolescents and Young Adults (AYAs) with Cancer - National Cancer Institute', 'Information about cancer in adolescents and young adults (AYAs), including treatment, follow-up care, coping, and related research.', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/types/aya', 'a243647da5d36b6311d6b57ee394a401'),
(549, 'Emotional Support for Young People with Cancer  - National Cancer Institute', 'Information to help young people find emotional and psychological support after a cancer diagnosis and during cancer treatment. Includes advice on talking with mental health experts, recognizing signs', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/types/aya/support', '7eb75d1214987a4a8a143b24b3651037'),
(550, 'Young People Facing End-of-Life Care Decisions  - National Cancer Institute', 'End-of-life care conversations and decisions are important for young people with end-stage cancer or terminal cancer. If cancer is advanced, talk with your doctor about personal priorities, palliative', '', 'https://www.cancer.gov/types/aya/end-of-life', '4917e44112baeba1bd5f8f7e774d7e51'),
